distraction: I was not doing anything else while I was participating in the survey. I actually found it very hard to remember things so I had to concentrate a lot.
strategies: I used movie refs to help me remember things. Like the train with the fall leaves reminded me of Harry Potter and the crab/lobster thing was Sebastian from the little mermaid. So whenever the crab/lobster thing appeared it was Sebastian so if there was a Digger it was Sebastian doing construction work etc Also I'd name things like 'Space Bear' was easy for me to remember. Also stuff like the skis and the palm trees reminded me of vacation so that's how I connected that.
easier: Some things were very easy but I had a hard time remembering what the canoe was connected to. The rocket ship and the bear was easy; the Eagle and the train was easy bc that was 'Americanized Harry Potter. 'etc I think the objects I had the most trouble with were the canoe and the horse saddle. The easier objects were the crab/lobster; the rocket ship; the bear; the train; and the fall leaves. All the ocean themed objects were easier to connect.
similar: I have not participated in a similar study.
comments: The task was long and sometimes it was frustrating dragging things down into the gray box because it would constantly say I was overlapping a city but it was an interesting experiment.
